OL,3,CFire boss tribunal hears details of
OL,4,C'bullying and harassment' complaint
OL,6,FIn a subsequent meeting with assistant
OL,7,Fchief fire officer Mr Millington, it
OL,8,Fis alleged that he "adopted a very
OL,9,Fintimidating and bullying manner,
OL,10,Fraising his voice" and urged Mr
OL,11,FRoberts to "agree that he had
OL,12,Fcommitted misconduct by raising the
OL,13,Fmatter of nepotism".
OL,15,FAfter Mr Roberts made a complaint to
OL,16,Fthe service, it commissioned an
OL,17,Finvestigation through a third party
OL,18,Finvestigator.
